  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "To quickly unfollow people on Instagram, follow these steps:\n\n### On the **Instagram App**:\n1. **Open Instagram** and go to your **Profile** by tapping your profile picture in the bottom-right corner.\n2. Tap the **Following** count to see the list of accounts you follow.\n3. Use the **Search Bar** to find specific accounts or scroll through the list.\n4. Tap the **Following** button next to the account name and select **Unfollow** to stop following them.\n\n### Tips for Efficiency:\n1. **Default sorting**: Instagram lists the accounts you interact with the least at the top, so these might be good candidates for unfollowing.\n2. **Use Desktop**: Unfollowing can be faster on the web version of Instagram.\n\n### On **Instagram Desktop**:\n1. Go to [Instagram.com](https://www.instagram.com) and log in.\n2. Click your **Profile Picture** in the top-right corner, then select **Profile**.\n3. Click the **Following** count to see the list of accounts.\n4. Click the **Following** button next to an account and select **Unfollow**.\n\n### Additional Tools:\nIf you want to **mass unfollow** people, you can use third-party tools like **Cleaner for IG** (available for iOS/Android), but be cautious as these tools may violate Instagram's terms of service and risk your account being banned. Always use official methods to stay safe.\n\nRemember: Instagram limits the number of accounts you can unfollow in a short period to prevent spamming, so it may take time if you\u2019re unfollowing a lot of people.",
